From 5eef4e2af9f69f7fa912c655258015eba2ae5e08 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CrispStrobe <cze+github@mailbox.org>
Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 12:20:33 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(ggml-cpu): F16 mul_mat input saturation on ARM NEON
 (issue #38)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Upstream ggml-cpu's mul_mat for F16 weights × F32 inputs first
converts src1 (F32) to F16 via __fp16 cast, which saturates F32
values above 65504 to ±Inf. The Inf propagates through the dot
product and the next layer's RMSNorm produces NaN, even with an F32
accumulator. This poisons any model whose intermediate activations
exceed 65504 — most commonly an FFN's silu(gate)*up product, which
in a 3072-wide block can reach ~1.4e5 even when individual mul_mat
outputs are 200–400 in magnitude.

Symptom (geneing's reproducer in #38): qwen3-tts F16 talker on
--gpu-backend cpu emits NaN logits at code_predictor block 2's
ffn_down, the talker AR loop never samples codec_eos, runs to the
1500-frame cap and produces ~32 minutes of garbage. Q8_0 talker is
unaffected because its vec_dot path keeps src1 as F32 in the inner
loop. Apple Metal is unaffected for the same reason. Reproduced on
M1 with the public F16 GGUF (SHA256 9b71...d4c, byte-identical to
huggingface.co/cstr/qwen3-tts-0.6b-base-GGUF).

Fix: add ggml_vec_dot_f16_f32 (F16 weight × F32 input → F32 sum, NEON
+ AVX2/F16C + scalar) and route the F16 type traits through it with
vec_dot_type=F32. ggml_compute_forward_mul_mat then sees src1 already
matches vec_dot_type and skips the saturating F32→F16 quantize step.

Defence-in-depth: switch ggml_vec_dot_f16 (still called by
conv_transpose_1d_f16 etc. outside the type-traits dispatch) from
vfmaq_f16 to F32 accumulator via simd-mappings.h — the F16 register
accumulator can also overflow 65504 on long F16×F16 dot products.

Roundtrip (qwen3-asr-0.6b-q4_k transcribing post-fix F16 CPU TTS):
  prompt "Hello world."          → "Hello world."   ✓
  prompt "Hello world, this is …
   a quick test of the qwen
   three TTS model."             → "Hello world. This is a quick
                                    test of the Quinn Free TTS
                                    model."          ✓

LEARNINGS.md "F16 mul_mat input saturation on ARM NEON CPU" carries
the full diagnostic flow + verification recipe. Patches marked with
// CrispASR patch (issue #38) — MUST RE-APPLY after every ggml bump.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
